<div class="intro">
    <h1>Privacy Notice</h1>
    <p class="lead" style="font-size: 1.35rem; line-height: 1.45; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        Short, because there isn't much to say: no analytics, no third-party tracking,
        one strictly-necessary cookie.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="content-box" style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2>What this site collects</h2>
    <p>
        This site runs on <strong>Cloudflare Workers</strong>, which sits in front of every
        request as a <em>data processor</em> — it necessarily sees request metadata (IP
        address, User-Agent, request path, timestamps) to serve pages and protect the
        site from abuse. That processing is standard for any web host and is <strong>not
        shared with, or used by, any analytics or advertising service</strong> — this site
        runs none. An IP address is personal data under GDPR even without a cookie, which
        is why this notice exists at all despite the small footprint below.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="content-box" style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2>The one cookie this site sets</h2>
    <p>
        A single cookie, <code>we_gate</code>, is set only after you submit the entry
        code on the splash gate. It is a signed token that simply remembers "this browser
        already typed the code" for <strong>30 days</strong>, so you aren't asked again on
        every visit. It carries no identity, no tracking ID, and no third party ever reads
        it.
    </p>
    <p>
        Because <code>we_gate</code> is <strong>strictly necessary</strong> for the site to
        function (there is no content to show without it) and nothing else is set, this
        falls under the ePrivacy "strictly necessary" exemption — <strong>no cookie-consent
        banner is required</strong>, and none is shown.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="content-box" style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2>What isn't here</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>No analytics (no Google Analytics, no Cloudflare Zaraz, no first-party pixel).</li>
        <li>No advertising or retargeting cookies.</li>
        <li>No third-party embeds that set their own cookies.</li>
        <li>No account system, no forms that collect personal data beyond the entry code above.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        If that ever changes — an analytics tool, a Zaraz integration, any additional
        cookie — this notice will be rewritten first and a consent banner added before the
        change ships. Until then, the honest answer is that there is very little to
        disclose.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="content-box">
    <h2>Questions</h2>
    <p>
        This project is currently the work of a single author (see
        <a href="/governance/">Governance</a>). For a privacy question, open an issue on
        <a href="https://github.com/chalbert/webeverything">the GitHub repo</a>.
    </p>
</div>
